      "content": "That's exactly what I'm looking for. If we call it a \"security hardening exercise,\" it turns a failure into a strength. \n\nOne thing though—if the tech reporters ask specifically for details on why the \"refresh\" resulted in user emails being briefly accessible, what's our line? I want to make sure we have a specific, technical-sounding explanation ready that doesn't involve mentioning the S3 misconfiguration at all. What's the best lie—I mean, what's the best \"technical reality\" we can give them?",
